<div>
  <h1>ORF Finder App</h1>
  <p>ORF-Finder is a library that finds the longest Open Reading Frame (ORF) from a nucleotide sequence.</p>

  <p>It will search the sequence for existing start and stop codons and return the longest ORF for each frame (if there multiple with the same size, then all are shown).</p>

  <p>The source code of the ORF-Finder library is at github under <a target="_blank" href="http://github.com/averissimo/orf_finder">averissimo/orf_finder</a>.</p>
</div>

<div>
  <%= render 'form' %>
</div>

<h2 class="gray no-bold">Results</h2>
<div id="results">
  <%- if @results %>
    <%= render 'search_results' %>
  <%- else %>
  <p class="gray no-results">Submit form above to see results</p>
  <%- end  %>
</div>

