<h2>How does it work?</h2>

<p>It searches the sequence for existing <em>start</em> and <em>stop</em> codons and return a single ORF for each frame.</p>

<p>When there is not an ORF present with any of the configurated start and stop codons, then it fallbacks to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Using the first codon of the sequence when:</li>
  <ul>
    <li>No start codon is present;</li>
    <li>The lenght of an ORF is shorter than the minimum option;</li>
  </ul>
  <li>Using the last codon of the sequence when:</li>
  <ul><li>No stop codon is present.</li></ul>
</ul>
